	<hr WIDTH="100%">
	<h2>Introduction:</h2>
	This lab exercises the ability to perform repetition via <i>nested</i> <b><tt>for</tt></b> loops.<br>
	We will use nested loops to generate <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ASCII_art"><i>ASCII-art</i></a>
	right triangles exhibiting each of the four possible rectilinear orientations.

	<h3>Lab 10 Assignment:</h3>
	<ul> 
	    <li> Create a new directory, <b><tt>Lab10</tt></b>, in your class account directory.</li> 
	    <li> Move into your <tt>Lab10</tt> directory.</li>
	    <li> Create the file <tt>ASCII_triangles.html.</tt>
	    <li> Use HTML comments at the top of this file identifying:</li> 
	    <ul> 
		<li>where the file is located (e.g. <tt>~/cs200999/labs/Lab10/ASCII_triangles.html</tt>)</li> 
		<li>the author (<i>you</i>) </li> 
		<li>what the program does</li> 
		<li>when you created the file</li> 
		<li>when you last modified the file</li> 
	    </ul> 
	    <li>When implementing your program, as often as is practical, repeat the following steps:</li> 
	    <ol> 
		<li> modify your Web page file via the editor</li> 
		<li> save the file</li> 
		<li> refresh the browser open to your Web page</li> 
		<li> verify that your modifications did what you've intended</li> 
	    </ol> 
	    <li>Title your Webpage appropriately.
	</ul>
	
	<ul>
	    <li>Provide a documented <u>textbox</u> for the user to enter a size indicating the number of asterisks to use on a side for the four ASCII-art right triangles.</li>
	    <li>Use a pair of <i>nested</i><tt>for</tt> loops to generate the following ASCII-art right triangles:<br>
	    (<i>Shown using a value of 4 asterisks per side</i>)<br>
	    <pre>
	    ****
	    ***
	    **
	    *

	    *
	    **
	    ***
	    ****

	    ****
	     ***
	      **
	       *

	       *
	      **
	     ***
	    ****
	    </pre>
	    </li>
	    <li>Display the total number of asterisks used to form each shape.</li>
	    <li>Repeat the above making the triangles hollow.<br>
	    (<i>Shown using a value of 5 asterisks per side</i>)<br>
	    <pre>
	    *****
	    *  *
	    * *
	    **
	    *

	    *
	    **
	    * *
	    *  *
	    *****

	    *****
	     *  *
	      * *
	       **
		*

		*
	       **
	      * *
	     *  *
	    *****
	    </pre>
	    </li> 
	    <li>Display the total number of asterisks used to form each shape.</li>
	</ul>



	Ensure that in your code identifiers (e.g. variable and function names) are labeled appropriately.<br>

	<b>Hint</b>: <i>remember that a blank is itself a character that occupies a character's worth of space</i>.

	<p>

	When finished, submit your exercise solution <u>Web page</u> and its <u>screenshot</u> to the dropbox.

